[quote=“TabbyKiller, post:4, topic:268955”][quote author=newb pk3r link=topic=354869.msg2717894#msg2717894 date=1237755827]

Yes i use to have this problem. Double click it and you will see Use the web service and select a programme and stuff

Well click the bottom one.(select a programme)

When there is the next box that comes up.
Untick the box that is ticked on the bottom left. And run it under notepad.

thanks will this let the server for others can play now?
[/quote]

No thats to fix your client.java

To turn on your server for others. Either turn on your source from your source files.

IMPORTANT!: You have to open up your no-ip conduct and tick your servers box.[/quote]
